Cell.Text: [S] Welcome to the family, lad. I'm expecting you to make us a lot of coin, so don't disappoint me.
[S] Welcome to the family, lass. I'm expecting you to make us a lot of coin, so don't disappoint me.

[S] Simple. Do as your told and keep your blade clean. We can't turn a profit by killing. | You should talk with Delvin Mallory and Vex. They know their way around this place and they'll be able to kick some extra jobs your way. | Oh, and talk to Tonilia in the Flagon... she'll set you up with your new armor.

Node.Caption: TG02BrynjolfStartupBranchTopic01: So how do I get my cut of the spoils?

Cell.Text: The Guild depends on an arrangement of influential people to keep things running smoothly.

Node.Caption: TG02BrynjolfQuestStartBranchTopic03a: What's so important about these clients?

Cell.Text: Goldenglow Estate is a bee farm; they raise the wretched little things for honey. It's owned by some smart-mouth Wood Elf named Aringoth. | We need you to teach him a lesson by burning down three of the estate's hives and clearing out the safe in the main house.

Node.Caption: TG02BrynjolfQuestStartBranchTopic03: Tell me about the Goldenglow job.

Cell.Text: The catch is that you can't burn the whole place to the ground. | That important client Mercer mentioned would be furious if you did.
That's not how things work around here. The Guild depends on an arrangement of influential people to keep things running smoothly.

Node.Caption: TG02BrynjolfQuestStartBranchTopic06: Who cares, we're the Thieves Guild.

Cell.Text: [S] Aye, the last thing we want to be doing is crossing our clients.
[S] Maven prefers that Aringoth remains alive, but if he tries to stop you from getting the job done, kill him. | The Guild has a lot riding on this. Don't make me look foolish by mucking it up.
[S] Without them at our backs, we'd be in serious trouble.
Hey, I'm not done talking to you yet. Come back here!
